{"_path":"/blog/2023/06/request-animation-frame","_dir":"06","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"en","title":"Let's find out about requestAnimationFrame()","description":"In order to implement animation that is difficult to express with CSS alone, JavaScript must be used, and using it without optimization can cause p...","createdAt":"2023-06-11 21:30","updatedAt":"2023-06-12 13:44","isPublished":true,"cover":"https://wbwsloxpaolxwerwiupa.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-asset/images/d037121a-a7cf-471c-a511-999f7f146450.webp","tags":["Javascript","Animation","Wiki"],"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Before we start, we need to use some terms repeatedly, but it's long, so let's define it as a contraction."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"setTimeout()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"setInterval()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" => "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"timer function"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"requestAnimationFrame()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" => "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rAF()"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"hr","props":{"id":""},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In order to implement animation that is difficult to express with CSS alone, JavaScript must be used, and using it without optimization can cause performance problems.\nPrior to the release of "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rAF()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" api, the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"timer function"}]},{"type":"text","value":" was used as an optimization technique, and since then, "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rAF()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" has been used."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this article, we will check what problems the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"timer function"}]},{"type":"text","value":" has and compare it with "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rAF()"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"frame-loss"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Frame loss"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Since the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"timer function"}]},{"type":"text","value":" operates without considering the frame, it cannot guarantee when the callback function is called.\nTherefore, if it runs over two frames as shown in the figure below, the animation will not be smooth because it misses one frame."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"v-prose-img","props":{"alt":"Frame loss graph. source - https://web.dev/optimize-javascript-execution","src":"https://wbwsloxpaolxwerwiupa.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-asset/images/54dfd618-50c9-463e-aa62-dd1919651fd6.webp"},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tag":"v-alert","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"💡 "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How does 16ms in the figure come from?"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nIf you didn't specifically choose refresh rate and buy it, you would be using a monitor at 60Hz refresh rate, which means that the screen is "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"refreshing itself 60 times every second"}]},{"type":"text","value":".\nTherefore, the screen is updated at intervals of 1,000 ms/60 times ≈ "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"16 ms"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"On the other hand, "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rAF()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is synchronized with the screen scan rate and is executed when the browser is ready to draw the screen.\nTo be more specific, the callback function written in "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rAF()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is registered in the Animation Frame queue, and all callback functions in this queue are processed at once "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"just before the next repaint"}]},{"type":"text","value":".\nAccordingly, it is possible to prevent a problem in which a frame is lost because the callback function is started in the middle."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"v-iframe","props":{"src":"https://stackblitz.com/edit/web-platform-jujfzt?ctl=1&embed=1&file=example1.html","style":"height: 560px"},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Using the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"timer function"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rAF()"}]},{"type":"text","value":", we made an animation in which each box moves 5 px to the right, a total of 1,000 px, as an example code.\nAs mentioned earlier, the timer function is not guaranteed when the callback function will be executed, so frame loss may or may not occur enough to be visually confirmed. In this case, it can be confirmed by repeating it several times."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"waste-of-system-resources"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Waste of system resources"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"timer function"}]},{"type":"text","value":" also works within an inactive window or hidden iframe, wasting system resources, resulting in battery life and performance degradation problems.\nHowever, using "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rAF()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" saves system resources by stopping work when the window becomes inactive."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To see this for yourself, let's switch the browser to another tab as soon as we run the animation of the example code mentioned above.\nIf you wait for about 5 seconds and go back, the animation run with the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"timer function"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is already over, but the function run with the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rAF()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" starts again from the spot."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"raf-performance-optimization"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rAF()"}]},{"type":"text","value":" performance optimization"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{"className":"language-js material-theme-lighter_material-theme-ocean","code":"window.addEventListener('scroll', function(e) {\n\n  if (!ticking) {\n    window.requestAnimationFrame(function() {\n      doSomething();\n      ticking = false;\n    });\n\n    ticking = true;\n  }\n});\n","language":"js","meta":""},"children":[{"type":"element","